<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-09-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="352" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/575.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Foreign Affairs
                                    of Guatemala</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-09-17"><hi rend="italic">September 17,
                                    1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I have the honor to advise your excellency that the international bureau
                            of Central American Republics was inaugurated to-day in accordance with
                            the convention signed at Washington.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Barrios.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>